    <fr:title text="The Ackermann function by Löb induction">The Ackermann function by Löb induction</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The Ackermann function
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[A{\mathopen {}\left (0, n\right )\mathclose {}} = n+1,
   \quad 
   A{\mathopen {}\left (m+1, 0\right )\mathclose {}} = A{\mathopen {}\left (m, 1\right )\mathclose {}},
   \quad 
   A{\mathopen {}\left (m+1, n+1\right )\mathclose {}} = A{\mathopen {}\left (m,\, A{\mathopen {}\left (m+1, n\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>
is total but not primitive recursive, and its recursion is not
structural: the <html:em>result</html:em> of the inner call indexes the outer
call.</html:p>
    <html:p><fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FS/" title="Löb induction on families" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FS/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FS/" type="local">Löb induction on families</fr:link> over
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N} \times  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> with the <html:em>lexicographic</html:em> order
shows it terminates.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
