            <fr:route>/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FS/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Löb induction on families">Löb induction on families</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Like <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FR/" title="Later on families" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FR/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FR/" type="local">later on families</fr:link>, the recursion principle for
families is inherited from that on presheaves. Given a family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and a step
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\varphi _x : \rhd _{\mathrm {Fam}} A\,{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}} \to  A{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}
   \quad \text {for each } x,]]></fr:tex>
the construction is a chain of transpositions with
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" title="Löb induction for presheaves on a direct category" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FP/" type="local">Löb for presheaves</fr:link> used in the middle:
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {aligned}
   &\mathrm {Fam}{\mathopen {}\left (\rhd _{\mathrm {Fam}} A,\; A\right )\mathclose {}}
     && \\
   =\;\; &\mathrm {Fam}{\mathopen {}\left (U \rhd  \mathrm {Cofree} A,\; A\right )\mathclose {}}
     && \text {definition of } \rhd _{\mathrm {Fam}} \\
   \cong \;\; &\mathsf {Psh}\,\mathcal {C}{\mathopen {}\left (\rhd  \mathrm {Cofree} A,\; \mathrm {Cofree} A\right )\mathclose {}}
     && U \dashv  \mathrm {Cofree} \\
   \longrightarrow \;\; &\mathsf {Psh}\,\mathcal {C}{\mathopen {}\left (\top ,\; \mathrm {Cofree} A\right )\mathclose {}}
     && \text {L\"ob} \\
   \cong \;\; &\mathrm {Fam}{\mathopen {}\left (\top ,\; A\right )\mathclose {}}
     && U \dashv  \mathrm {Cofree},\; U \top  = \top 
   \end {aligned}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
            <html:p>Just as for presheaves, the fixed point constructed above is
<html:em>unique</html:em>: the two transpositions are bijections, and the
presheaf-level fixed point is already unique.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
